      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While minor tenderness can be normal, the presence of any discharge should be checked by a professional to rule out infection, even if it's small. Self-treating with Neosporin and a warm towel might not address a developing issue, potentially leading to complications. Because Sydney has excellent healthcare options, please take a moment to call your doctor's office for advice or book a telehealth consultation first. They can advise you on whether a clinic visit is truly necessary.",
      "source": "target",
